{
  "texts": [
    "In essence, text summarization is the process of generating concise and fluent summaries while maintaining the content and overall meaning of key information.",
    "Currently, two distinct types of this task exist: extractive summarization and abstractive summarization.",
    "RA-DIT (Lin et al., 2023b) employs the CNN/DailyMail dataset to refine the language model component of the model, which demonstrates remarkable efficacy in the text summarization task due to the operation of command finetuning.",
    "In contrast, Self-Mem (Cheng et al., 2024) was trained using the XSum and BigPatent datasets.",
    "The authors observed that memory enhancement had a significantly larger effect on BigPatent than XSum."
  ]
}